</location>
</area>
</region>
 was turned into a shrine where a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../777/560777.xml">
memorial</link> was held for his thousands of loyal fans, many in tears, paid their respects to the gallant Canadien. His funeral was held at the Forum, and it was broadcast all over Canada. Thousands later lined the funeral cortege as Howie's body was taken for burial.</p>
<p>

On <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../764/21764.xml">
November 3</link>, 1937, the Howie Morenz Memorial Game was played at the Forum, to raise money for the Morenz family.  A combined team of Canadiens and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../009/240009.xml">
Montreal Maroons</link> was defeated 6–5 by a team comprised of all-stars from the other six teams then in operation in the NHL (the <diversion wordnetid="100426928" confidence="0.8">
